Key Match Events: Jamie Leweling scored the winner in the 64th minute after the Dutch failed to clear a corner.
Pre-Game Insights: Germany held a farewell tribute for Ilkay Gündogan, Manuel Neuer, Thomas Müller, and Toni Kroos following their retirements from international football.
Post-Match Reflections: Leweling stated, 'We won as a team. I scored but we played a good game and I am happy to have helped.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Dutch failed to muster a shot on target in the first period but improved after the break and both Xavi Simons and Donyell Malen had major chances to snatch a scarcely deserved point in the closing stages.
